\label{thm:symp_weyl_equalities}
    Let $A, B \in \mathbb{P}_{2n}(\mathbb{R})$ and $i,j \in \{1,\ldots, n\}$ be any indices such that $i+j-1 \leq n$. 
    Then the equality holds in \eqref{symp_weyl_inequalities}, i.e.,
    \begin{equation}\label{symp_weyl_equalities}
        d_{i+j-1}(A+B) = d_i(A) + d_j(B),
    \end{equation}
    if and only if there exists a common normalized symplectic eigenvector pair of $A$, $B$, and $A+B$ corresponding to their symplectic eigenvalues $d_i(A)$, $d_j(B)$, and $d_{i+j-1}(A+B)$.

